1 (i) defines chronic absenteeism;
2 (ii) identifies and analyzes trends in data on attendance and chronic
3 absenteeism at the State and local level;
4 (iii) includes an analysis of how student attendance is collected in
5 local school systems across the State; and
6 (iv) describes the most effective practices for identifying, preventing,
7 and eliminating chronic absenteeism that are culturally responsive and nonpunitive.
8 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
9 1, 2025. It shall remain effective for a period of 1 year and 6 months and, at the end of
10 December 31, 2026, this Act, with no further action required by the General Assembly, shall
11 be abrogated and of no further force and effect.

